Let $z = x + yi,$ where $x$ and $y$ are real numbers.  Then $|z - 3| = |x + yi - 3| = |x - 3 + yi| = \sqrt{(x - 3)^2 + y^2}$ and
\[|z + 3| = |x + yi + 3| = |x + 3 + yi| = \sqrt{(x + 3)^2 + y^2},\]so
\[\sqrt{(x - 3)^2 + y^2} = 2 \sqrt{(x + 3)^2 + y^2}.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[(x - 3)^2 + y^2 = 4[(x + 3)^2 + y^2].\]This simplifies to $x^2 - 6x + 9 = 4x^2 + 24x + 36,$ or $3x^2 + 30x + 27 = 0.$  This factors as $3(x + 3)(x + 9) = 0,$ so $x = -3$ or $x = -9.$
If $x = -3,$ then $(x - 3)^2 + y^2 = 36$ represents a circle centered at 0 with radius 6.
If $x = -9,$ then $(x - 3)^2 + y^2 = 144$ represents a circle centered at 0 with radius 12.
