The circle $|z| = k$ will intersect each of these circles in exactly one point if it is tangent to one of them.  This occurs when the distance between the center of the circle $|z| = k$ and each of the points $-3$ and $-9$ is equal to $k.$  Hence, $k = 6$ or $k = 12.$
Therefore, the possible values of $k$ are $\boxed{6,12}.$
The answer is 6,12.
